//This folder is intended to contain only UVM agent-related components used in the verification environment.

//Purpose
//The agents/ directory is used to organize all UVM agents in a structured and reusable manner. Each protocol or interface-specific agent should be placed in its own subfolder.

//Recommended Structure
//agents/
// ├── ethernet_agent/
// │    ├── ethernet_driver.sv
// │    ├── ethernet_monitor.sv
// │    ├── ethernet_sequencer.sv
// │    ├── ethernet_sequence_item.sv
// │    ├── ethernet_agent.sv
// │    └── sequences/
// │         ├── ethernet_base_seq.sv
// │         └── ethernet_random_seq.sv
// │
// ├── apb_agent/
// │    ├── apb_driver.sv
// │    ├── apb_monitor.sv
// │    ├── apb_sequencer.sv
// │    ├── apb_sequence_item.sv
// │    ├── apb_agent.sv
// │    └── sequences/
//Rules and Guidelines
//Only UVM agent-related files should be placed inside this folder.
//Every agent should contain:
//   Driver
//   Monitor
//   Sequencer
//   Sequence Item (Transaction)
//   Agent class

//Sequences should be organized inside a dedicated sequences/ folder.

//Follow consistent naming conventions for all agent components.
//Keep agents reusable and protocol-independent wherever possible.
//Avoid placing environment, testbench top, scoreboard, or test files inside this directory.
//Naming Convention
//
//Use protocol-based naming for clarity.
//
//Example:
//
//ethernet_driver.sv
//ethernet_monitor.sv
//ethernet_sequencer.sv
//ethernet_sequence_item.sv

//Objective
//Maintaining a clean and consistent agent structure improves:
//Readability
//Reusability
//Team collaboration
//Ease of debugging and maintenance
